# Calculated Fields

## Project Title

**Strategic Product Placement Analysis Using Tableau**

---

# Introduction

Calculated fields in Tableau are custom formulas used to create new measures and dimensions from the existing dataset. They help perform business calculations, create KPIs, categorize products, and enhance dashboard interactivity.

---

# 1. Total Revenue

### Formula

```tableau
SUM([Revenue])
```

### Description

Calculates the total revenue generated from all products.

---

# 2. Total Units Sold

### Formula

```tableau
SUM([Units_Sold])
```

### Description

Calculates the total quantity of products sold.

---

# 3. Average Selling Price

### Formula

```tableau
AVG([Price])
```

### Description

Calculates the average selling price of all products.

---

# 4. Average Discount

### Formula

```tableau
AVG([Discount])
```

### Description

Calculates the average discount percentage given on products.

---

# 5. Revenue Per Unit

### Formula

```tableau
SUM([Revenue]) / SUM([Units_Sold])
```

### Description

Shows the average revenue generated from each unit sold.

---

# 6. Estimated Profit

### Formula

```tableau
SUM([Revenue]) * 0.25
```

### Description

Assumes a 25% profit margin and estimates total profit.

---

# 7. Total Products

### Formula

```tableau
COUNTD([Product_ID])
```

### Description

Counts the total number of unique products.

---

# 8. Total Customers (Approximation)

### Formula

```tableau
COUNT([Customer_Age])
```

### Description

Counts the total customer transactions in the dataset.

---

# 9. Average Customer Age

### Formula

```tableau
AVG([Customer_Age])
```

### Description

Calculates the average age of customers.

---

# 10. Sales Category

### Formula

```tableau
IF SUM([Units_Sold]) >= 200 THEN "High Sales"
ELSEIF SUM([Units_Sold]) >= 100 THEN "Medium Sales"
ELSE "Low Sales"
END
```

### Description

Categorizes products based on the number of units sold.

---

# 11. Revenue Category

### Formula

```tableau
IF SUM([Revenue]) >= 100000 THEN "High Revenue"
ELSEIF SUM([Revenue]) >= 50000 THEN "Medium Revenue"
ELSE "Low Revenue"
END
```

### Description

Groups products according to revenue generated.

---

# 12. Discount Category

### Formula

```tableau
IF [Discount] >= 20 THEN "High Discount"
ELSEIF [Discount] >= 10 THEN "Medium Discount"
ELSE "Low Discount"
END
```

### Description

Classifies products based on discount percentage.

---

# 13. Customer Age Group

### Formula

```tableau
IF [Customer_Age] <= 20 THEN "Teen"
ELSEIF [Customer_Age] <= 35 THEN "Young Adult"
ELSEIF [Customer_Age] <= 50 THEN "Adult"
ELSE "Senior"
END
```

### Description

Creates customer age groups for demographic analysis.

